WEBVTT

00:04.838 --> 00:05.573
OH, COME ON.
GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME.

00:05.606 --> 00:06.574
I'M JUST TRYING
TO HELP YOU, DAD.

00:06.607 --> 00:10.378
YEAH, WELL, I THINK YOU
HELPED ME QUITE ENOUGH.

00:10.411 --> 00:11.512
IS GRANDPA GONNA DIE?

00:11.545 --> 00:12.746
OH, YEAH.
CUT IT OUT.

00:12.780 --> 00:14.348
NO,
HE'S NOT GONNA DIE,

00:14.382 --> 00:16.284
NOW, JUST PLEASE
SIT DOWN, DAD.

00:16.317 --> 00:17.351
I CAN'T SIT DOWN!

00:17.385 --> 00:19.653
OH, YEAH, I FORGOT.
YOU'RE MORTALLY WOUNDED.
WHOO.

00:19.687 --> 00:21.622
THIS PLACE
IS ALL MOBBED UP.

00:21.655 --> 00:22.356
WE'RE GONNA
BE HERE FOREVER.

00:22.390 --> 00:24.358
UH-UH.
I'M TAKING CARE
OF THIS.

00:24.392 --> 00:25.726
WE NEED A DOCTOR
RIGHT AWAY.

00:25.759 --> 00:27.228
WHAT'S THE NATURE
OF THE EMERGENCY?

00:27.261 --> 00:28.429
OH, WAIT. WAIT.
THERE'S NO EMERGENCY HERE.

00:28.462 --> 00:29.497
SURE THERE IS.
NO, NO, NO.

00:29.530 --> 00:31.165
IT'S NOT TRUE. NO.
IT'S VERY TRUE.

00:31.199 --> 00:32.400
NO, IT'S
NOT AN EMERGENCY.

00:32.433 --> 00:34.835
DON'T YOU REMEMBER?
THAT'S WHY WE CAME
TO THE EMERGENCY ROOM,

00:34.868 --> 00:37.305
TO GET THAT FAST
EMERGENCY SERVICE.

00:37.338 --> 00:38.406
TELL YOU WHAT.

00:38.439 --> 00:39.840
FILL THESE OUT
AND HAVE A SEAT.

00:39.873 --> 00:45.413
NICE WORK.
WE'VE BEEN TRIAGED,
DUMB-ASS.

00:45.446 --> 00:46.414
WHAT'S "TRIAGE"?

00:46.447 --> 00:48.249
IT MEANS
GET USED TO THE SMELL
OF DISINFECTANT,

00:48.282 --> 00:50.218
'CAUSE WE'RE
GONNA BE HERE ALL NIGHT.

00:50.251 --> 00:53.187
I LIKE IT.
IT MAKES ME DIZZY.

00:53.654 --> 00:56.624
DON'T WORRY.
I KNOW HOW TO MOVE
THIS THING ALONG.

00:56.657 --> 00:58.526
DAD,
CRY OUT IN ANGUISH.

00:58.559 --> 00:59.093
WHAT?

00:59.127 --> 01:01.662
JUST, YOU KNOW...
AAH!

01:03.731 --> 01:05.133
IT WAS HIM.

01:05.166 --> 01:06.667
GRANDPA,
CAN I GET YOU ANYTHING?

01:06.700 --> 01:10.238
UH, THANKS, JIMMY.
I'LL HAVE A GINGER ALE.

01:10.271 --> 01:11.772
I'LL HAVE A COKE.

01:11.805 --> 01:14.175
IS YOUR NAME GRANDPA?

01:16.344 --> 01:17.345
OH, OFFICER!

01:17.378 --> 01:18.779
OFFICER?
YES?

01:18.812 --> 01:19.747
HEY, DAD,
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

01:19.780 --> 01:23.184
I WANT THIS MAN ARRESTED
FOR ATTEMPTED MURDER!

01:40.168 --> 01:42.436
HE ATTACKED ME--
MY OWN SON!

01:42.470 --> 01:43.371
I DIDN'T ATTACK YOU!

01:43.404 --> 01:45.873
DAD, WE REALLY GOTTA
BRING THE LAW INTO THIS?

01:45.906 --> 01:47.308
AREN'T YOU THE GUY I SAW--

01:47.341 --> 01:49.177
NO, IT WASN'T ME.

01:49.210 --> 01:50.878
I COULD SWEAR--

01:50.911 --> 01:51.845
I GOT THAT KIND OF FACE.

01:51.879 --> 01:53.514
I LOOK LIKE
A LOT OF GUYS...

01:53.547 --> 01:55.716
GUYS THAT AREN'T ME.

01:59.553 --> 02:00.921
WHAT ARE YOU READING?

02:00.954 --> 02:03.857
CIGAR AFICIONADO.

02:03.891 --> 02:04.925
DON'T THEY HAVE
ANYTHING ELSE?

02:04.958 --> 02:06.294
IF THERE WERE
ANYTHING ELSE,

02:06.327 --> 02:08.796
WOULD I BE READING
CIGAR AFICIONADO?

02:08.829 --> 02:11.265
WHAT ABOUT THIS?

02:11.299 --> 02:12.700
THAT'S PORNO.

02:12.733 --> 02:13.701
IT'S NOT PORNO.

02:13.734 --> 02:15.703
IT'S A MAGAZINE
FOR A MAN

02:15.736 --> 02:17.171
IN THE NEW MILLENNIUM

02:17.205 --> 02:19.940
IT'S NOTHING BUT PICTURES
OF NAKED BIMBOS.

02:19.973 --> 02:22.843
HALF-NAKED...ACTRESSES.

02:23.611 --> 02:27.448
IS MY FATHER-IN-LAW
GONNA SEE A DOCTOR
ANYTIME SOON?

02:27.481 --> 02:30.718
HE'S ON THE LIST.
SOMEONE WILL SEE HIM SHORTLY.

02:33.321 --> 02:35.256
YOU'RE BLOWING ME OFF,
AREN'T YOU?

02:35.289 --> 02:36.457
NO.

02:36.490 --> 02:39.727
I HAPPEN TO BE A HOSTESS
IN A VERY POPULAR
SOHO RESTAURANT,

02:39.760 --> 02:42.396
AND I BLOW PEOPLE OFF
ALL DAY LONG.

02:42.430 --> 02:43.130
I KNOW BLOWING OFF,

02:43.163 --> 02:45.466
AND YOU
ARE BLOWING ME OFF.

02:45.499 --> 02:49.337
MA'AM, WE'LL GET TO YOU
AS SOON AS WE CAN.

02:49.370 --> 02:54.675
SEE, THAT'S
EXACTLY WHAT I SAY!

02:55.676 --> 02:57.945
DAD, WILL YOU
LEAVE THIS GUY ALONE?!

02:57.978 --> 02:59.747
NO. I WANT HIM TO HEAR THIS.

02:59.780 --> 03:03.884
IT WAS MY GRANDSON JIMMY'S
BIRTHDAY PARTY.

03:03.917 --> 03:04.785
Claudia: YEAH!

03:04.818 --> 03:08.689
ALL RIGHT. HEY, BUDDY,
THIS ONE IS FROM US.

03:08.722 --> 03:11.892
LILY, IT'S
YOUR BROTHER'S BIRTHDAY.

03:11.925 --> 03:12.793
GET OFF THE PHONE.

03:12.826 --> 03:15.296
NOW SHE'S TELLING ME
TO GET OFF THE PHONE.

03:15.329 --> 03:18.966
NOW SHE'S GIVING ME
THIS LOOK SHE DOES.

03:18.999 --> 03:21.535
I KNOW. I KNOW.

03:21.569 --> 03:23.237
ON WHEELS.

03:23.271 --> 03:27.408
NOW SHE'S
TAKING THE PHONE
AND HANGING IT UP.

03:29.677 --> 03:32.446
COOL!
IT'S A REAL SNARE DRUM.

03:32.480 --> 03:34.615
THAT'S THE KIND
PETER CRISS PLAYS.

03:34.648 --> 03:35.416
WHO?

03:35.449 --> 03:37.285
YOU CAN PLAY WITH THAT
LATER, JIMMY.

03:37.318 --> 03:41.622
NOW, SAVING THE BEST
FOR LAST.

03:41.655 --> 03:42.256
WHOA.

03:42.290 --> 03:43.424
Sean: HEY, WHAT IS IT, DAD?

03:43.457 --> 03:44.224
HE'S GONNA LOVE IT.

03:44.258 --> 03:46.827
IT'S FROM BOTH OF US.
NO, IT'S NOT.

03:46.860 --> 03:50.398
ALL RIGHT!
IT'S A BB GUN!

03:50.431 --> 03:53.033
A BB GUN.
A BB GUN.

03:53.066 --> 03:55.369
WHOA.

03:57.838 --> 04:01.041
OF COURSE HE COULDN'T STAND
THAT JIMMY LIKED
MY GIFT BETTER.

04:01.074 --> 04:02.510
WRONG. WRONG.
WHAT I CAN'T STAND

04:02.543 --> 04:04.278
IS THAT YOU THINK
YOU KNOW BETTER THAN ME

04:04.312 --> 04:06.414
ABOUT WHAT I SHOULD DO
WITH MY FAMILY!

04:06.447 --> 04:08.048
WELL,
THAT'S BECAUSE I DO!

04:08.081 --> 04:10.984
OH, YEAH, RIGHT.
LIKE THAT TIME HENRY
HAD THE NOSEBLEED?

04:11.018 --> 04:13.921
TILT HIM FORWARD.
HE'S GOT TO LEAN
INTO THE FLOW.

04:13.954 --> 04:14.822
NO, DAD, THAT'S NOT RIGHT.

04:14.855 --> 04:16.357
COME ON, HENRY,
JUST LEAN YOUR HEAD BACK.

04:16.390 --> 04:17.525
YOU'LL CHOKE HIM
THAT WAY.

04:17.558 --> 04:20.060
NO--NO, I WON'T. LOOK,
JUST TILT YOUR HEAD BACK
AND RELAX.

04:20.093 --> 04:20.828
THAT'S THE--
FORWARD!

04:20.861 --> 04:22.730
NO, DAD, I'M HIS DAD.
I SAY BACK!

04:22.763 --> 04:23.964
IT'S GOTTA BE FORWARD!
IT'S GOTTA BE BACK!

04:23.997 --> 04:26.534
LOOK, I KNOW
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT!

04:26.567 --> 04:27.868
HE'S MY SON!
HE GOES BACK!

04:29.770 --> 04:32.640
FORWARD DOESN'T
MAKE ANY SENSE.
THINK ABOUT IT!

04:32.673 --> 04:34.542
ASK ANY DOCTOR
IN THIS PLACE.

04:34.575 --> 04:36.644
OH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.
YOU KNOW EVERYTHING.

04:36.677 --> 04:37.611
HEY, HEY, HEY!

04:37.645 --> 04:38.412
YOU'RE NOT HERE BECAUSE
OF A NOSEBLEED, RIGHT?

04:38.446 --> 04:40.481
RIGHT.
SO WHAT ARE WE
TALKING ABOUT?

04:40.514 --> 04:41.415
WELL,
WHAT WE'RE TALKING ABOUT

04:41.449 --> 04:43.050
IS HE NEVER RESPECTS
MY JUDGMENT ON ANYTHING.

04:43.083 --> 04:45.619
WHAT WE'RE TALKING ABOUT
IS A BB GUN, OK,

04:45.653 --> 04:48.456
THAT SHOULD NEVER
HAVE BEEN IN OUR HOUSE.

04:52.593 --> 04:53.861
WHAT IS OUR POLICY
ON THIS?

04:53.894 --> 04:56.830
UH, WE DON'T HAVE
A POLICY ON THIS.

04:56.864 --> 04:57.665
WE DON'T HAVE POLICIES.

04:57.698 --> 05:00.501
OH, COME ON.
ALL PARENTS HAVE POLICIES.

05:00.534 --> 05:01.301
WE MUST HAVE SOME.

05:01.335 --> 05:03.437
I DON'T KNOW, BABE.
IT'S JUST A TOY.

05:03.471 --> 05:05.739
IT'S SHAPED LIKE A GUN.

05:05.773 --> 05:06.774
YEAH, WELL, SO IS FLORIDA,

05:06.807 --> 05:08.909
AND WE DON'T HAVE
A POLICY ON THAT.

05:08.942 --> 05:10.077
THAT'S A COMPELLING ARGUMENT.

05:10.110 --> 05:12.646
WELL, I MEAN, IT'S JUST
JIMMY SEEMS TO LOVE
THIS THING,

05:12.680 --> 05:15.349
AND I DON'T WANT TO BE
THE JERK WHO TAKES IT
AWAY FROM HIM.

05:15.383 --> 05:18.018
BESIDES,
HE'S PRETTY RESPONSIBLE,
DON'T YOU THINK?

05:18.051 --> 05:19.019
YEAH, THAT'S TRUE.

05:19.052 --> 05:20.988
I MEAN, HE WAS GREAT
WITH THAT WOOD-BURNING SET.

05:21.021 --> 05:24.392
WELL...

05:27.628 --> 05:28.529
UH...

05:28.562 --> 05:31.932
IT'S OK.
WE WON'T TELL
YOUR MOM ABOUT THIS.

05:33.667 --> 05:37.505
MAYBE HE'S NOT READY
FOR A BB GUN.

05:38.939 --> 05:41.842
ALL RIGHT.
NOW YOU GOT IT.

05:41.875 --> 05:45.012
OH, HEY,
LOOK WHAT I CAN DO.

05:46.680 --> 05:47.948
Claudia: WOW.
THAT'S REALLY GREAT.

05:47.981 --> 05:51.051
THAT DRUM WE GAVE YOU
IS PRETTY COOL,
TOO, HUH?

05:51.084 --> 05:51.852
YEAH.

05:51.885 --> 05:54.488
HEY, JIMMY, CAN I PLAY
YOUR NEW DRUM?

05:54.522 --> 05:55.689
YOU CAN HAVE IT.

05:56.690 --> 05:58.058
UH, HEY, JIMMY,
I KNOW HOW MUCH

05:58.091 --> 05:59.660
YOU'RE ENJOYING
YOUR NEW TOY.

05:59.693 --> 06:00.594
WHAT?

06:00.628 --> 06:01.729
WELL, YOUR MOTHER AND I
HAVE BEEN TALKING...

06:01.762 --> 06:06.133
YOU'RE GONNA TAKE AWAY
MY FAVORITE PRESENT
OF ALL TIME?

06:06.166 --> 06:07.334
NO, WELL,
WE'RE NOT TAKING IT AWAY.

06:07.367 --> 06:11.004
WHAT WE THINK IS MAYBE
YOU JUST SHOULDN'T HAVE IT
RIGHT NOW.

06:11.038 --> 06:14.408
I WOULDN'T GIVE MY GRANDSON
SOMETHING THAT'S NOT SAFE.

06:14.442 --> 06:15.809
DAD, I'M NOT
SUGGESTING YOU WOULD.

06:15.843 --> 06:16.577
IT'S A GREAT GIFT,

06:16.610 --> 06:17.411
AND HE'S HAD A LOT
OF FUN WITH IT.

06:17.445 --> 06:18.979
OH, YEAH,
THESE LAST COUPLE OF MINUTES

06:19.012 --> 06:20.914
ARE SOMETHING
HE'LL TREASURE FOREVER.

06:20.948 --> 06:24.685
DAD, THIS IS
MY FAVORITE PRESENT.

06:24.718 --> 06:26.086
DON'T YOU GUYS TRUST ME?

06:26.119 --> 06:28.922
OF COURSE WE DO.
WE TRUST YOU.

06:28.956 --> 06:32.826
I PROMISE THAT I WILL BE
SUPER CAREFUL WITH IT.

06:32.860 --> 06:35.195
PLEASE?

06:35.228 --> 06:36.664
WELL, HE PROMISED
TO BE CAREFUL.

06:36.697 --> 06:39.467
HE IS WEARING
THE GOGGLES.

06:46.540 --> 06:48.442
IF I HAD TAKEN IT
AWAY FROM HIM THEN,

06:48.476 --> 06:49.843
WE'D BE HOME IN BED NOW.

06:49.877 --> 06:51.111
Jimmy: OH, GRANDPA.

06:51.144 --> 06:52.713
OH, THANKS, JIMMY.

06:52.746 --> 06:53.614
AND, DAD.

06:53.647 --> 06:54.982
YOU GOT ME A SODA?

06:55.015 --> 06:55.949
YEAH.

06:55.983 --> 06:57.785
THANKS, BUDDY.

06:57.818 --> 06:59.620
AAH! OH!

06:59.920 --> 07:04.892
OK, OK, I'M GONNA PRETEND
THAT YOU SHOOK THAT UP
ACCIDENTALLY.

07:04.925 --> 07:07.861
I'LL PRETEND THAT, TOO.

07:07.895 --> 07:10.097
HE'S JUST
A LITTLE OVERTIRED.

07:10.130 --> 07:11.565
YEAH, AND HE HATES ME.

07:11.599 --> 07:13.567
YEAH,
IT'S PROBABLY MORE THAT.

07:13.601 --> 07:14.267
COME ON, GUYS.

07:14.301 --> 07:15.035
LET'S GO
TO THE VENDING MACHINE

07:15.068 --> 07:17.204
AND GET YOU
SOMETHING TO EAT, OK?

07:17.237 --> 07:18.572
DOES IT HAVE LASAGNA?

07:18.606 --> 07:20.474
NO, IT'S
A SNACK MACHINE, HONEY.

07:20.508 --> 07:24.111
LASAGNA CAN BE A SNACK
IF YOU DON'T EAT A LOT OF IT.

07:24.144 --> 07:26.814
GOOD POINT.

07:29.149 --> 07:31.151
OK, WHAT MAKES HER
ATTRACTIVE?

07:31.184 --> 07:34.087
SHE'S GOT
A SENSE OF MYSTERY.

07:34.121 --> 07:35.756
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
MYSTERY?

07:35.789 --> 07:37.257
SEE HOW SHE'S
GOT HER THUMB HOOKED

07:37.290 --> 07:38.225
IN HER BIKINI STRING
THERE?

07:38.258 --> 07:41.629
IS SHE PULLING IT UP?
IS SHE PULLING IT DOWN?

07:41.662 --> 07:44.765
MAYBE SHE JUST LIKES
HAVING HER THUMBS THERE.

07:44.798 --> 07:45.533
YEAH.

07:45.566 --> 07:48.068
OH, LOOK, SOUP.
THEY'VE GOT SOUP.

07:48.101 --> 07:49.269
YOU LIKE SOUP.

07:49.302 --> 07:50.070
IS IT GOOD SOUP?

07:50.103 --> 07:52.640
ARE YOU KIDDING?
THIS IS A HOSPITAL.

07:52.673 --> 07:56.644
ARE YOU SURE YOU GUYS
CAN TRUST ME WITH HOT SOUP?

07:56.677 --> 07:59.547
JIMMY, IT'S NOT
THAT WE CAN'T TRUST YOU.

07:59.580 --> 08:02.182
LOOK, I KNOW
THE PAST COUPLE OF DAYS
HAVE BEEN HARD FOR YOU,

08:02.215 --> 08:05.786
BUT I WANT YOU TO KNOW
YOUR FATHER AND I
ARE NOT MAD AT YOU.

08:05.819 --> 08:07.655
OH, I KNOW.
I'M MAD AT YOU.

08:07.688 --> 08:11.692
WELL, YOU CAN
HAVE SOUP ANYWAY.

08:19.567 --> 08:21.101
OH, COME ON!

08:21.134 --> 08:23.571
IT'S MIDNIGHT.
MY CHILDREN ARE HUNGRY.

08:23.604 --> 08:24.938
I NEED YOUR SOUP.

08:24.972 --> 08:26.574
SEE, IF I HAD
MY BB GUN RIGHT NOW,

08:26.607 --> 08:29.943
WE COULD SHOOT THE SOUP
OUT OF THERE.

08:29.977 --> 08:30.778
COOL.

08:30.811 --> 08:33.146
COME ON. WE GOTTA GET
OUR MONEY BACK.

08:33.180 --> 08:35.783
OK, WELL, EDDIE,
HOW ABOUT HER?

08:35.816 --> 08:37.918
WELL, UM...

08:37.951 --> 08:40.253
SHE'S ALL RIGHT.
HER WHOLE ATTITUDE SAYS,

08:40.287 --> 08:42.089
"HEY,
I'M DOWN WITH THAT."

08:42.122 --> 08:43.190
DOWN WITH WHAT?

08:43.223 --> 08:44.558
EXACTLY.

08:44.592 --> 08:46.059
YOU SEE HER?

08:46.093 --> 08:49.029
HER WHOLE ATTITUDE SAYS,
"HEY, I'M A NURSE."

08:49.062 --> 08:51.932
DOESN'T HER UNIFORM
SAY THAT?

08:51.965 --> 08:52.833
YOU KNOW IT.

08:52.866 --> 08:57.104
SEE, UNIFORMS ARE
A MAJOR THING FOR GUYS.

08:57.137 --> 08:57.805
OH, GREAT.

08:57.838 --> 08:58.471
THE ONLY UNIFORM
I GET TO WEAR

08:58.505 --> 09:00.340
IS A CATHOLIC SCHOOL
UNIFORM.

09:00.373 --> 09:03.076
WHAT GUY
IS GONNA LIKE THAT?

09:08.015 --> 09:09.917
WHAT'S WITH
ALL THE QUESTIONS?

09:09.950 --> 09:11.585
NOTHING.

09:11.619 --> 09:14.121
ALL RIGHT.

09:14.154 --> 09:16.123
WELL, IF YOU MUST KNOW,

09:16.156 --> 09:17.725
CHRISTINA AND I
WERE HANGING OUT

09:17.758 --> 09:19.026
IN FRONT OF MOCHA JOJO'S
TONIGHT,

09:19.059 --> 09:24.297
AND THESE 2 CUTE JERKS
WOULDN'T STOP BOTHERING US.

09:25.633 --> 09:26.734
HEY.

09:26.767 --> 09:28.268
HEY.

09:28.301 --> 09:29.637
HEY.

09:29.670 --> 09:31.872
HEY.

09:31.905 --> 09:33.807
YEAH, THAT SOUNDS
REALLY ANNOYING.

09:33.841 --> 09:35.876
WELL, THEN THEY
STOPPED BOTHERING ME,

09:35.909 --> 09:38.612
BUT THEY KEPT BOTHERING
CHRISTINA.

09:38.646 --> 09:40.781
HEY, CHRISTINA,
CHECK THIS OUT.

09:40.814 --> 09:43.016
YOU GUYS ARE STUPID.

09:43.050 --> 09:44.051
NO,
YOU'RE STUPID.

09:44.084 --> 09:45.285
YEAH, YOU'RE STUPID.

09:45.318 --> 09:48.789
YOU GUYS ARE BOTH STUPID.

09:49.923 --> 09:52.726
MORONS.

09:52.760 --> 09:54.828
WHAT IS WITH YOUR FRIEND?

09:54.862 --> 09:56.764
I DON'T KNOW.

10:00.067 --> 10:02.736
I MEAN, WHAT'S SO GREAT
ABOUT CHRISTINA?

10:02.770 --> 10:04.772
HER FOREHEAD IS,
LIKE, AN ACRE.

10:04.805 --> 10:08.075
YOU COULD
PROJECT A MOVIE ON IT.

10:08.108 --> 10:09.076
HASN'T SHE HEARD OF BANGS?

10:09.109 --> 10:12.145
YEAH, I CAN SEE
HOW THAT WOULDN'T
BOTHER YOU.

10:12.179 --> 10:13.881
I SAID IT DIDN'T BOTHER ME.

10:13.914 --> 10:15.282
HAVEN'T YOU BEEN LISTENING?

10:15.315 --> 10:17.785
OK.

10:19.352 --> 10:21.655
EXCUSE ME. HELLO!

10:21.689 --> 10:23.657
YOUR LITTLE SOUP MACHINE
ATE MY MONEY

10:23.691 --> 10:24.658
AND DIDN'T GIVE MY SON
ANY SOUP.

10:24.692 --> 10:26.860
I'M SORRY.
WE'VE BEEN HAVING
PROBLEMS WITH IT.

10:26.894 --> 10:29.096
WELL, YOU COULD HAVE
PUT A SIGN ON IT.

10:29.129 --> 10:30.664
IT WORKS SOME OF THE TIME.

10:30.698 --> 10:33.667
OH. DIDN'T REALIZE
THIS WAS A GAME OF CHANCE.

10:33.701 --> 10:36.737
I WOULD HAVE WORN
MY LUCKY SWEATER.

10:36.770 --> 10:39.740
DO YOU HAVE
ANY LASAGNA BACK THERE?

10:40.874 --> 10:43.210
YOU PUT ME
IN AN IMPOSSIBLE POSITION.

10:43.243 --> 10:46.179
I DON'T KNOW WHY
YOU MADE SUCH A BIG DEAL
ABOUT A TOY.

10:46.213 --> 10:49.249
OH, YOU SHOULD HAVE SEEN
WHAT THIS TOY DID.

10:57.758 --> 11:00.327
JIMMY!

11:11.438 --> 11:13.707
PULL!

11:32.192 --> 11:35.763
OH, BETTER GET ME
A PRIEST.

11:35.796 --> 11:37.497
THIS BB IS ON THE MOVE.

11:37.530 --> 11:39.166
NO, IT'S NOT.

11:39.199 --> 11:40.834
ONCE IT GETS
INTO MY BLOODSTREAM,

11:40.868 --> 11:42.135
IT CAN GO
STRAIGHT TO THE BRAIN.

11:42.169 --> 11:45.172
YEAH, IT'S ALREADY
LODGED IN YOUR BRAIN.

11:45.205 --> 11:47.941
LOOK! I HAVE OTHER THINGS
I COULD BE DOING.

11:47.975 --> 11:49.509
IF YOU HAVE NOTHING MORE
TO TELL ME, THEN--

11:49.542 --> 11:53.346
NO, NO. I AM THE VICTIM
OF AN ASSAULT.

11:53.380 --> 11:55.949
THEN CAN WE JUST
GET ON WITH IT, PLEASE?

11:55.983 --> 11:57.084
YES. ALLOW ME.

11:57.117 --> 11:59.452
Sean: JIMMY,
YOU SHOULDN'T SHOOT
PERFECTLY GOOD FRUIT.

11:59.486 --> 12:00.420
I KNOW. I'M SORRY.

12:00.453 --> 12:03.924
IT'S JUST SO COOL
WHEN THE JUICE SQUIRTS OUT.

12:03.957 --> 12:05.125
IT'S LIKE BLOOD.

12:05.158 --> 12:07.194
YOU KNOW,
I CAN'T ARGUE WITH THAT.
JUST DON'T DO IT AGAIN.

12:07.227 --> 12:07.961
NO, DON'T THROW IT OUT.

12:07.995 --> 12:08.996
JUST PICK THE BBs OUT
AND EAT IT.

12:09.029 --> 12:12.900
OH, YEAH, DAD?
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO
WITH THIS?

12:12.933 --> 12:14.067
HUH?

12:14.101 --> 12:15.502
YOUR FATHER'S RIGHT,
JIMMY,

12:15.535 --> 12:17.938
JUST BECAUSE THE DRUM
ISN'T YOUR FAVORITE PRESENT

12:17.971 --> 12:21.341
